           instead.


@{b}NOTES@{ub}
@{fg shine}       This function is called by all functions which evaluate INI file
       context item data. It is, in fact, a low level function. The given
       buffer must have a mininum size of 128 bytes.
       If no buffer is given, the new one must be freed with @{"iniFreeNameStr" Link "iniFreeNameStr"}()

@{fg text}
@{b}BUGS@{ub}
@{fg shine}
@{fg text}
@{b}SEE ALSO@{ub}
       @{"iniGetContextName" Link "iniGetContextName"}(), @{"iniGetContextItem" Link "iniGetContextItem"}(), iniContextItemDataA(),
       <@{"libraries/ini_lib.h" Link "INCLUDE:libraries/ini_lib.h/Main" 0}>



@ENDNODE


@NODE "iniGetContextItemDataA" "ini.library/iniGetContextItemDataA"

